<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870107-0100 </DOCNO><HL> Pan Am December Traffic Rose</HL><DD> 01/07/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> PNAIRLINES (AIR) </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Pan American World Airways said its December traffic rose 1.7% to 1.82 billion revenue passenger miles from 1.79 billion a year earlier.    The year-earlier figures exclude Pan Am's Pacific division, which was sold at the end of 1985.    A revenue passenger mile is one paying passenger carried one mile.    Pan Am's December load factor, or percentage of available seats filled, declined slightly to 55.8% from 56.3% in 1985.    For the full year, traffic rose 4.2% to 21.5 billion revenue passenger miles from 20.63 billion in 1985. Full-year load factor was 52.9%, down from 61.2%. </TEXT></DOC>